  "articleBody": "&lt;p&gt;We spend too much time staring at our phones&mdash;just ask the pedestrians we almost walk into on a daily basis. If scrolling through your Newsfeed or swiping right were Olympic sports, we&rsquo;d definitely take home a medal. But in reality, the only things getting a workout in either case are our thumbs. That&rsquo;s not to say your phone can&rsquo;t help you lead a healthier, happier life. You just need to know the right apps to download. &lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;Before you fall down the rabbit hole that is the app store, check out our list of the best health and fitness apps. We tested out hundreds before whittling it down to the 39 that are really worth checking out. (Some are repeats from &lt;a href=&quot;http://greatist.com/live/best-health-and-fitness-apps-2015&quot;&gt;last year&rsquo;s list&lt;/a&gt;, but there are plenty of newbies as well.) &lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Note: This list is presented in no particular order. To check out the methodology we used to determine which apps made the cut, scroll to the bottom.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;section class=&quot;slideshow list-image-left&quot;  &gt;
            &lt;h3 class=&quot;subhead&quot;&gt;Fitness&lt;/h3&gt;
          
            &lt;div class=&quot;slide&quot;&gt;
        
        &lt;div class=&quot;title-wrapper&quot;&gt;
          &lt;h4&gt;
                          &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;http://www.c25k.com&quot;&gt;1. Couch to 5K &lt;/a&gt;
                      &lt;/h4&gt;
                  &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;slide-body&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p&gt;&lt;span
  class=&quot;media media-element-container media-g_tiny_float_left&quot;
  &gt;
    &lt;img
    src=&quot;http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/mini_content/public/c25k.png?itok=5oz-JhGR&quot;

          alt=&quot;c25k&quot;
    
        class=&quot;media-element file-g-tiny-float-left&quot;
  /&gt;

  
  &lt;/span&gt;If you&rsquo;ve wanted to try running but never known where to start, Couch to 5K should be the next app you download. The free eight-week program gives users three workouts per week that get you ready for your local Turkey Trot or Fourth of July road race. (Free; &lt;a href=&quot;https://itunes.apple.com/au/app/c25k-5k-trainer-free-go-from/id485971733?mt=8&quot;&gt;iOS&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.c25k&amp;amp;hl=en&quot;&gt;Android&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
          
            &lt;div class=&quot;slide&quot;&gt;
        
        &lt;div class=&quot;title-wrapper&quot;&gt;
          &lt;h4&gt;
                          &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;http://www.blogilates.com&quot;&gt;2. Blogilates&lt;/a&gt;
                      &lt;/h4&gt;
                  &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;slide-body&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p&gt;&lt;span
  class=&quot;media media-element-container media-g_tiny_float_left&quot;
  &gt;
    &lt;img
    src=&quot;http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/mini_content/public/blogilates.png?itok=ZSrBRKKn&quot;

          alt=&quot;Blogilates&quot;
    
        class=&quot;media-element file-g-tiny-float-left&quot;
  /&gt;

  
  &lt;/span&gt;We first fell in love with &lt;a href=&quot;http://greatist.com/health/most-influential-health-fitness-people&quot;&gt;Cassey Ho&lt;/a&gt; while watching her Blogilates videos on YouTube. This app takes things to the next level&mdash;you get access to all of her videos, plus an online forum and monthly workout calendar. (Free with optional in-app purchases; &lt;a href=&quot;https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/blogilates-official-app/id677023207?mt=8&quot;&gt;iOS&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=co.veam.veam31000015&amp;amp;hl=en&quot;&gt;Android&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
          
            &lt;div class=&quot;slide&quot;&gt;
        
        &lt;div class=&quot;title-wrapper&quot;&gt;
          &lt;h4&gt;
                          &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;https://zombiesrungame.com&quot;&gt;3. Zombies, Run!&lt;/a&gt;
                      &lt;/h4&gt;
                  &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;slide-body&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p&gt;&lt;span
  class=&quot;media media-element-container media-g_tiny_float_left&quot;
  &gt;
    &lt;img
    src=&quot;http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/mini_content/public/zombies-run.png?itok=zBhpF8nI&quot;

          alt=&quot;Zombies, Run!&quot;
    
        class=&quot;media-element file-g-tiny-float-left&quot;
  /&gt;

  
  &lt;/span&gt;Running becomes way more fun when each step gets you closer to carrying out your mission, collecting materials for your base camp, and keeping humans safe from the zombie apocalypse. There&rsquo;s a reason this game became the highest-grossing health and fitness app on iTunes in just two weeks&mdash;even though it&rsquo;s free to download, you&rsquo;ll start shelling out money like you do for Candy Crush. Except this game helps you get your sweat on. (Free with optional in-app purchases; &lt;a href=&quot;https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/zombies-run!/id503519713?mt=8&quot;&gt;iOS&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.sixtostart.zombiesrunclient&amp;amp;hl=en&quot;&gt;Android&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;


        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
          
            &lt;div class=&quot;slide&quot;&gt;
        
        &lt;div class=&quot;title-wrapper&quot;&gt;
          &lt;h4&gt;
                          &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;http://fit.net&quot;&gt;4. Fitnet&lt;/a&gt;
                      &lt;/h4&gt;
                  &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;slide-body&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p&gt;&lt;span
  class=&quot;media media-element-container media-g_tiny_float_left&quot;
  &gt;
    &lt;img
    src=&quot;http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/mini_content/public/fitnet.png?itok=44ZxjyU1&quot;

          alt=&quot;Fitnet&quot;
    
        class=&quot;media-element file-g-tiny-float-left&quot;
  /&gt;

  
  &lt;/span&gt;Fitnet is the workout app for people who can&rsquo;t carve out time to go to the gym. The app features an abundance of five- and seven-minute targeted workouts, so you don&rsquo;t have to sacrifice time with your friends and family to achieve your fitness goals. Plus, the app uses your phone&rsquo;s camera for a whole new kind of selfie&mdash;this one measures how closely you follow the moves shown on the screen. (Free with optional in-app purchases; &lt;a href=&quot;https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/fitnet-personal-trainer/id718444936?mt=8&quot;&gt;iOS&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=net.fit.app&amp;amp;hl=en&quot;&gt;Android&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
          
            &lt;div class=&quot;slide&quot;&gt;
        
        &lt;div class=&quot;title-wrapper&quot;&gt;
          &lt;h4&gt;
                          &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;http://sworkit.com&quot;&gt;5. Sworkit&lt;/a&gt;
                      &lt;/h4&gt;
                  &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;slide-body&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p&gt;&lt;span
  class=&quot;media media-element-container media-g_tiny_float_left&quot;
  &gt;
    &lt;img
    src=&quot;http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/mini_content/public/sworkit_0.png?itok=INFzHFTl&quot;

          alt=&quot;Sworkit&quot;
    
        class=&quot;media-element file-g-tiny-float-left&quot;
  /&gt;

  
  &lt;/span&gt;Tell Sworkit the type of workout you&rsquo;re looking for (strength, cardio, yoga, or stretching) and the amount of time you&rsquo;ve got (anywhere from five minutes to an hour), and the app delivers the moves to follow during your sweat session. If you opt for premium ($4.99 per month), the app lets you get even more personalized, by setting the number of reps and the areas of the body you want to focus on. (Free with optional in-app purchases; &lt;a href=&quot;https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/sworkit-daily-circuit-training/id527219710?mt=8&amp;amp;ign-mpt=uo%3D4&quot;&gt;iOS&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=sworkitapp.sworkit.com&quot;&gt;Android&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
          
            &lt;div class=&quot;slide&quot;&gt;
        
        &lt;div class=&quot;title-wrapper&quot;&gt;
          &lt;h4&gt;
                          &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;http://www.motiontraxx.com&quot;&gt;6. Motion Traxx&lt;/a&gt;
                      &lt;/h4&gt;
                  &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;slide-body&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p&gt;&lt;span
  class=&quot;media media-element-container media-g_tiny_float_left&quot;
  &gt;
    &lt;img
    src=&quot;http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/mini_content/public/motion-traxx.jpeg?itok=QXrhvaHR&quot;

          alt=&quot;MotionTraxx&quot;
    
        class=&quot;media-element file-g-tiny-float-left&quot;
  /&gt;

  
  &lt;/span&gt;Listening to music can be the perfect way to add extra oomph to your workout, but crafting the perfect playlist is tricky. That&rsquo;s where Motion Traxx comes in. The app combines coaching from world-class trainers with music designed to set the perfect intensity for every phase of your workout. (Free with optional in-app purchases; &lt;a href=&quot;https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/motion-traxx-fitness-cardio/id905096566?mt=8&quot;&gt;iOS&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.motiontraxx.motiontraxxand&amp;amp;hl=en&quot;&gt;Android&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
          
            &lt;div class=&quot;slide&quot;&gt;
        
        &lt;div class=&quot;title-wrapper&quot;&gt;
          &lt;h4&gt;
                          &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;http://stronglifts.com&quot;&gt;7. StrongLifts 5x5&lt;/a&gt;
                      &lt;/h4&gt;
                  &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;slide-body&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p&gt;&lt;span
  class=&quot;media media-element-container media-g_tiny_float_left&quot;
  &gt;
    &lt;img
    src=&quot;http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/mini_content/public/stronglifts-5x5.png?itok=Ho9yZVj7&quot;

          alt=&quot;Stronglifts 5x5&quot;
    
        class=&quot;media-element file-g-tiny-float-left&quot;
  /&gt;

  
  &lt;/span&gt;No need to carry around a paper and pencil while lifting at the gym anymore. This app keeps track of the exercise, number of reps, and rest time, so all you have to worry about is getting to the gym and getting &lt;s&gt;huge&lt;/s&gt; stronger. (Free with optional in-app purchases; &lt;a href=&quot;https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/stronglifts-5x5-simplest-most/id488580022?mt=8&quot;&gt;iOS&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.stronglifts.app&amp;amp;hl=en&quot;&gt;Android&lt;/a&gt;) &lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
          
            &lt;div class=&quot;slide&quot;&gt;
        
        &lt;div class=&quot;title-wrapper&quot;&gt;
          &lt;h4&gt;
                          &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;https://www.strava.com/&quot;&gt;8. Strava Running and Cycling&lt;/a&gt;
                      &lt;/h4&gt;
                  &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;slide-body&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p&gt;&lt;span
  class=&quot;media media-element-container media-g_tiny_float_left&quot;
  &gt;
    &lt;img
    src=&quot;http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/mini_content/public/strava.png?itok=JhouQZQK&quot;

          alt=&quot;Strava&quot;
    
        class=&quot;media-element file-g-tiny-float-left&quot;
  /&gt;

  
  &lt;/span&gt;If you&rsquo;re a serious runner or cyclist, you need one place to keep track of your most recent runs and rides, and no app comes close to the capabilities offered by Strava. The app can track distance, speed, elevation, calories burned, heart rate, power, and cadence. Then it synthesizes all of this data into easy-to-understand graphics. (Free with optional in-app purchases; &lt;a href=&quot;https://itunes.apple.com/app/strava-cycling/id426826309?mt=8&quot;&gt;iOS&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.strava&quot;&gt;Android&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
          
            &lt;div class=&quot;slide&quot;&gt;
        
        &lt;div class=&quot;title-wrapper&quot;&gt;
          &lt;h4&gt;
                          &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;https://www.spotify.com/us/running/&quot;&gt;9. Spotify Running&lt;/a&gt;
                      &lt;/h4&gt;
                  &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;slide-body&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p&gt;&lt;span
  class=&quot;media media-element-container media-g_tiny_float_left&quot;
  &gt;
    &lt;img
    src=&quot;http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/mini_content/public/spotify.png?itok=wOvaW7PD&quot;

          alt=&quot;Spotify Running&quot;
    
        class=&quot;media-element file-g-tiny-float-left&quot;
  /&gt;

  
  &lt;/span&gt;Part of the Spotify app (and let&rsquo;s be honest, you probably already have that on your phone), Spotify Running measures your pace and picks a song with the beats per minute to match it. It&rsquo;s about time your music matches your cadence instead of the other way around. (Free; &lt;a href=&quot;https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/spotify-music/id324684580?mt=8&quot;&gt;iOS&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.spotify.music&amp;amp;hl=en&quot;&gt;Android&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
          
            &lt;div class=&quot;slide&quot;&gt;
        
        &lt;div class=&quot;title-wrapper&quot;&gt;
          &lt;h4&gt;
                          &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;http://www.yonder.it/download/&quot;&gt;10. Yonder&lt;/a&gt;
                      &lt;/h4&gt;
                  &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;slide-body&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p&gt;&lt;span
  class=&quot;media media-element-container media-g_tiny_float_left&quot;
  &gt;
    &lt;img
    src=&quot;http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/mini_content/public/yonder.png?itok=Kaog0ixs&quot;

          alt=&quot;Yonder&quot;
    
        class=&quot;media-element file-g-tiny-float-left&quot;
  /&gt;

  
  &lt;/span&gt;Think of this like Yelp for the outdoor enthusiast. Enter your location and find dozens of suggestions for hiking, biking, kayaking, and skiing with reviews and tips from fellow outdoorsmen and women. (Free; &lt;a href=&quot;https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/yonder-outdoor-adventures/id643341612?mt=8&quot;&gt;iOS&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.yonder.android&amp;amp;hl=en&quot;&gt;Android&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
          
            &lt;div class=&quot;slide&quot;&gt;
        
        &lt;div class=&quot;title-wrapper&quot;&gt;
          &lt;h4&gt;
                          &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;https://www.dailyyoga.com/&quot;&gt;11. Daily Yoga&lt;/a&gt;
                      &lt;/h4&gt;
                  &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;slide-body&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p&gt;&lt;span
  class=&quot;media media-element-container media-g_tiny_float_left&quot;
  &gt;
    &lt;img
    src=&quot;http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/mini_content/public/daily-yoga.png?itok=98QiD8Nd&quot;

          alt=&quot;Daily Yoga&quot;
    
        class=&quot;media-element file-g-tiny-float-left&quot;
  /&gt;

  
  &lt;/span&gt;Never be bored by yoga again: More than 50 classes shot in HD video are just a few taps away. Each sequence has a specific focus, from increasing flexibility to strengthening your core. Plus, there&rsquo;s a library with detailed videos of more than 500 poses. (Free with optional in-app purchases; &lt;a href=&quot;https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/id545849922?mt=8&quot;&gt;iOS&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.dailyyoga.inc&quot;&gt;Android&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
          
            &lt;div class=&quot;slide&quot;&gt;
        
        &lt;div class=&quot;title-wrapper&quot;&gt;
          &lt;h4&gt;
                          &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/yoga-wake-up/id973221723?mt=8&quot;&gt;12. Yoga Wake Up&lt;/a&gt;
                      &lt;/h4&gt;
                  &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;slide-body&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p&gt;&lt;span
  class=&quot;media media-element-container media-g_tiny_float_left&quot;
  &gt;
    &lt;img
    src=&quot;http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/mini_content/public/yoga-wake-up.png?itok=25MIXWZ9&quot;

          alt=&quot;Yoga Wake Up&quot;
    
        class=&quot;media-element file-g-tiny-float-left&quot;
  /&gt;

  
  &lt;/span&gt;What better way to ease into the day than with a quick morning yoga flow? This app delivers a 10-minute sequence at your designated wake-up time. Each sequence is a little different. Some focus more on meditation, while others hone in on holding poses and setting intentions. Yoga every damn day just got a whole lot easier. (Free with optional in-app purchases; &lt;a href=&quot;https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/yoga-wake-up/id973221723?mt=8&quot;&gt;iOS&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
          
            &lt;div class=&quot;slide&quot;&gt;
        
        &lt;div class=&quot;title-wrapper&quot;&gt;
          &lt;h4&gt;
                          &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;http://www.nike.com/us/en_us/c/womens-training/apps/nike-training-club&quot;&gt;13. Nike+ Training Club&lt;/a&gt;
                      &lt;/h4&gt;
                  &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;slide-body&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p&gt;&lt;span
  class=&quot;media media-element-container media-g_tiny_float_left&quot;
  &gt;
    &lt;img
    src=&quot;http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/mini_content/public/nike-plus.png?itok=P8ukZ3Cw&quot;

          alt=&quot;Nike+ Training Club&quot;
    
        class=&quot;media-element file-g-tiny-float-left&quot;
  /&gt;

  
  &lt;/span&gt;Nike+ Training Club comes with all the things you&rsquo;d expect from a top-notch fitness app: workouts designed by professional trainers and athletes, customizable fitness programs, sharing capabilities to compare your progress with others, and a totally sleek interface. And in Nike fashion, it just does it better than the competition. (Free; &lt;a href=&quot;https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/nike+-training-club/id301521403?mt=8&quot;&gt;iOS&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.nike.ntc&amp;amp;hl=en&quot;&gt;Android&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
          
            &lt;div class=&quot;slide&quot;&gt;
        
        &lt;div class=&quot;title-wrapper&quot;&gt;
          &lt;h4&gt;
                          &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;https://www.endomondo.com/&quot;&gt;14. Endomondo&lt;/a&gt;
                      &lt;/h4&gt;
                  &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;slide-body&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p&gt;&lt;span
  class=&quot;media media-element-container media-g_tiny_float_left&quot;
