        class=&quot;media-element file-g-tiny-float-left&quot;
  /&gt;

  
  &lt;/span&gt;Cardio exercise can quickly get boring and repetitive. That&rsquo;s why Endomondo is so great. Set a goal for your run, walk, or bike ride, and the app&rsquo;s virtual trainer lets you know if you&rsquo;re on track to meet it or if you need to speed up. It&rsquo;s great to compete against yourself (and your goals), but it&rsquo;s even better when you can use Endomondo to challenge or cheer on friends. (Free with optional in-app purchases; &lt;a href=&quot;https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/running-walking-endomondo/id333210180?mt=8&quot;&gt;iOS&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.endomondo.android&amp;amp;hl=en&quot;&gt;Android&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
