  &gt;
    &lt;img
    src=&quot;http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/mini_content/public/talkspace.jpeg?itok=xLYNht54&quot;

          alt=&quot;Talkspace&quot;
    
        class=&quot;media-element file-g-tiny-float-left&quot;
  /&gt;

  
  &lt;/span&gt;Bet you didn&rsquo;t think you could chat with a therapist for just $25 per week. Well, Talkspace makes that possible. For that low fee, you can text with a trained professional as often as you need. They also offer services for individuals and couples. Oh, and the best part? You can do it from your couch. (Free with optional in-app purchases; &lt;a href=&quot;https://itunes.apple.com/app/id661829386?mt=8&quot;&gt;iOS&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.talkspace.talkspaceapp&quot;&gt;Android&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
          
            &lt;div class=&quot;slide&quot;&gt;
        
        &lt;div class=&quot;title-wrapper&quot;&gt;
          &lt;h4&gt;
                          &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;http://my.happify.com/&quot;&gt;31. Happify&lt;/a&gt;
                      &lt;/h4&gt;
                  &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;slide-body&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p&gt;&lt;span
  class=&quot;media media-element-container media-g_tiny_float_left&quot;
  &gt;
    &lt;img
    src=&quot;http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/mini_content/public/happify.jpeg?itok=hy3ATUp9&quot;

          alt=&quot;Happify&quot;
    
        class=&quot;media-element file-g-tiny-float-left&quot;
  /&gt;

  
  &lt;/span&gt;This app is like a gym membership for your emotional health. The first time you open Happify, you&rsquo;re prompted to select a track that best meets your needs, whether it's finding more &ldquo;me&rdquo; time or getting better at handling stress. Each track is designed by an expert using the latest scientific research and full of quick, daily activities, including games, mindful meditations, and assessments. (Free with optional in-app purchases; &lt;a href=&quot;https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/happify/id730601963?mt=8&quot;&gt;iOS&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.happify.happifyinc&amp;amp;hl=en&quot;&gt;Android&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
          
            &lt;div class=&quot;slide&quot;&gt;
        
        &lt;div class=&quot;title-wrapper&quot;&gt;
          &lt;h4&gt;
                          &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;https://www.relationup.com/&quot;&gt;32. Relationup&lt;/a&gt;
                      &lt;/h4&gt;
                  &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;slide-body&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p&gt;&lt;span
  class=&quot;media media-element-container media-g_tiny_float_left&quot;
  &gt;
    &lt;img
    src=&quot;http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/mini_content/public/relationup.jpg?itok=C_Gb36DZ&quot;

          alt=&quot;RelationUP&quot;
    
        class=&quot;media-element file-g-tiny-float-left&quot;
  /&gt;

  
  &lt;/span&gt;We all have moments when we need relationship advice. We often turn to friends, but sometimes it's best to call in the big guns. That's when Relationup comes to the rescue. The app lets you text with one of the qualified, prescreened relationship counselors, and it's cheaper than going to therapy. Counselors are available 24/7 to help you with anything that&rsquo;s troubling you, from a breakup to questions about a second date to family drama. Your first conversation is free, and they run $12 per 15 minutes thereafter. (Free with optional in-app purchases; &lt;a href=&quot;https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/relationup-get-live-help-from/id1006899801?mt=8&amp;amp;ign-mpt=uo%3D4&quot;&gt;iOS&lt;/a&gt;) &lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
          
            &lt;div class=&quot;slide&quot;&gt;
        
        &lt;div class=&quot;title-wrapper&quot;&gt;
          &lt;h4&gt;
                          &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;http://www.7cups.com&quot;&gt;33. 7 Cups &lt;/a&gt;
                      &lt;/h4&gt;
                  &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;slide-body&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p&gt;&lt;span
  class=&quot;media media-element-container media-g_tiny_float_left&quot;
  &gt;
    &lt;img
    src=&quot;http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/mini_content/public/7cups.png?itok=-pJ3ezPI&quot;

          alt=&quot;7 Cups&quot;
    
        class=&quot;media-element file-g-tiny-float-left&quot;
  /&gt;

  
  &lt;/span&gt;Sometimes you just want to talk, and 7 Cups gives you an alternative to waking up your friends at 3 a.m. to vent about your annoying boss or significant other. The app offers fast, free responses from trained listeners. Now you can speak your mind without feeling judged whenever and wherever you need to. (Free; &lt;a href=&quot;https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/7-cups-anxiety-stress-depression/id921814681?mt=8&quot;&gt;iOS&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.sevencupsoftea.app&amp;amp;hl=en&quot;&gt;Android&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
                &lt;h3 class=&quot;subhead&quot;&gt;Overall Health&lt;/h3&gt;
          
            &lt;div class=&quot;slide&quot;&gt;
        
        &lt;div class=&quot;title-wrapper&quot;&gt;
          &lt;h4&gt;
                          &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;https://www.healthtap.com/&quot;&gt;34. HealthTap&lt;/a&gt;
                      &lt;/h4&gt;
                  &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;slide-body&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p&gt;&lt;span
  class=&quot;media media-element-container media-g_tiny_float_left&quot;
  &gt;
    &lt;img
    src=&quot;http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/mini_content/public/healthtap.png?itok=F4riEDVt&quot;

          alt=&quot;HealthTap&quot;
    
        class=&quot;media-element file-g-tiny-float-left&quot;
  /&gt;

  
  &lt;/span&gt;Next time you have a pressing medical concern (should I be worried about this rash?), don&rsquo;t ask Dr. Google. Turn to HealthTap instead. The app sends your question to its network of doctors, and one will answer you within a few hours. HealthTap also comes with a library of information on common ailments, so you can be better at spotting symptoms and picking the best remedy. And if you are looking for even more care, you can choose the prime membership ($99 per month), which allows you unlimited video and text chatting with doctors. (Free with in-app purchases; &lt;a href=&quot;https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/id466079030?&quot;&gt;iOS&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.healthtap.userhtexpress&quot;&gt;Android&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
          
            &lt;div class=&quot;slide&quot;&gt;
        
        &lt;div class=&quot;title-wrapper&quot;&gt;
          &lt;h4&gt;
                          &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;http://www.iodine.com/start&quot;&gt;35. Start&lt;/a&gt;
                      &lt;/h4&gt;
                  &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;slide-body&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p&gt;&lt;span
  class=&quot;media media-element-container media-g_tiny_float_left&quot;
  &gt;
    &lt;img
    src=&quot;http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/mini_content/public/start.jpeg?itok=fPrclts-&quot;

          alt=&quot;Start&quot;
    
        class=&quot;media-element file-g-tiny-float-left&quot;
  /&gt;

  
  &lt;/span&gt;If you&rsquo;re suffering from depression, it can take months upon months to find the right medicine (or drug cocktail) that works for you. Start aims to make that process a whole lot easier. The app includes a depression test, as well as programs to track your progress and the side effects of your medication&mdash;all helpful information to share with the medical professional treating you. (Free: &lt;a href=&quot;https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/id1012099928?_branch_match_id=246340427857593590&quot;&gt;iOS&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
          
            &lt;div class=&quot;slide&quot;&gt;
        
        &lt;div class=&quot;title-wrapper&quot;&gt;
          &lt;h4&gt;
                          &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;https://www.helloclue.com/&quot;&gt;36. Clue&lt;/a&gt;
                      &lt;/h4&gt;
                  &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;slide-body&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p&gt;&lt;span
  class=&quot;media media-element-container media-g_tiny_float_left&quot;
  &gt;
    &lt;img
    src=&quot;http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/mini_content/public/clue-app.jpg?itok=kb-R2WVL&quot;

          alt=&quot;Clue&quot;
    
        class=&quot;media-element file-g-tiny-float-left&quot;
  /&gt;

  
  &lt;/span&gt;Never be blindsided by your period again. Clue tracks your menstrual cycle, offering reminders before your next period. As Clue&rsquo;s algorithm finds the unique patterns of your own cycle, it will provide valuable insights for your everyday life. The app&rsquo;s designers also promise to never use flowers, butterflies, or euphemisms, so you can face your next period like an adult. (Free; &lt;a href=&quot;https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/clue-period-pms-tracker-health/id657189652?mt=8&quot;&gt;iOS&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.clue.android&amp;amp;hl=en&quot;&gt;Android&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
          
            &lt;div class=&quot;slide&quot;&gt;
        
        &lt;div class=&quot;title-wrapper&quot;&gt;
          &lt;h4&gt;
                          &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;http://www.sleepcycle.com/&quot;&gt;37. Sleep Cycle&lt;/a&gt;
                      &lt;/h4&gt;
                  &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;slide-body&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p&gt;&lt;span
  class=&quot;media media-element-container media-g_tiny_float_left&quot;
  &gt;
    &lt;img
    src=&quot;http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/mini_content/public/sleep_cycle_android_icon.png?itok=cN5EwJVa&quot;

          alt=&quot;Sleep Cycle&quot;
    
        class=&quot;media-element file-g-tiny-float-left&quot;
  /&gt;

  
  &lt;/span&gt;Say sayonara to feeling groggy in the morning. This app measures your sleep cycle, as its name suggests. Then it wakes you sometime during a 30-minute window before your alarm when you&rsquo;re in the lightest sleep state. Sure, you might get up before your alarm goes off, but you&rsquo;ll feel refreshed and ready to take on the day. (Free with in-app purchases on &lt;a href=&quot;https://itunes.apple.com/app/apple-store/id320606217?mt=8&quot;&gt;iOS&lt;/a&gt;, $0.99 on &lt;a href=&quot;https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.northcube.sleepcycle&quot;&gt;Android&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
          
            &lt;div class=&quot;slide&quot;&gt;
        
        &lt;div class=&quot;title-wrapper&quot;&gt;
          &lt;h4&gt;
                          &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;https://itunes.apple.com/app/id866001468&quot;&gt;38. Power Nap App&lt;/a&gt;
                      &lt;/h4&gt;
                  &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;slide-body&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p&gt;&lt;span
  class=&quot;media media-element-container media-g_tiny_float_left&quot;
  &gt;
    &lt;img
    src=&quot;http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/mini_content/public/power-nap-app2.jpeg?itok=xV7m9Gas&quot;

          alt=&quot;Power Nap App&quot;
    
        class=&quot;media-element file-g-tiny-float-left&quot;
  /&gt;

  
  &lt;/span&gt;If there are two things we love, it&rsquo;s &lt;a href=&quot;http://greatist.com/fitness/cat-turned-pro-soccer-goalie-video&quot;&gt;cats&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;http://greatist.com/live/naps-boost-productivity&quot;&gt;naps&lt;/a&gt;. The Power Nap App combines these natural gifts, complete with a timer (that only goes up to 30 minutes), pleasant sounds to help you sleep, and an alarm that gently wakes you back up, so you can rock the rest of your day. (Free; &lt;a href=&quot;https://itunes.apple.com/app/id866001468&quot;&gt;iOS&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
          
            &lt;div class=&quot;slide&quot;&gt;
        
        &lt;div class=&quot;title-wrapper&quot;&gt;
          &lt;h4&gt;
                          &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;https://www.leafly.com&quot;&gt;39. Leafly&lt;/a&gt;
                      &lt;/h4&gt;
                  &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;slide-body&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p&gt;&lt;span
  class=&quot;media media-element-container media-g_tiny_float_left&quot;
  &gt;
    &lt;img
    src=&quot;http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/mini_content/public/leafly.png?itok=gaU0oHzb&quot;

          alt=&quot;Leafly&quot;
    
        class=&quot;media-element file-g-tiny-float-left&quot;
  /&gt;

  
  &lt;/span&gt;This sleek app is the Wikipedia of weed, offering exhaustive information on thousands of marijuana strains, from Girl Scout Cookies (yes, that&rsquo;s a real strain) to Purple Urkle. It also offers directions to the nearest dispensary (in states where pot is legal) and regular updates on cannabis news. (Free; &lt;a href=&quot;https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/leafly-marijuana-strain-dispensary/id416456429?mt=8&quot;&gt;iOS&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=leafly.android&amp;amp;hl=en&quot;&gt;Android&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
